<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd">
<head>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="${context:css/examples/examples.css}"/>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>Stylesheets</h1>

	Styled with a <a href="http://www.w3.org/Style/CSS/">Cascading Style Sheet</a>, css/examples/examples.css.<br/><br/>
	
	Tapestry 5 includes its own stylesheet, assets/tapestry/default.css, at runtime.  Its aim is to format 
	validation errors. Its entries are unlikely to clash with ours because its entries all start with "t-".<br/><br/>
	
	References: 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/tapestry5/guide/css.html">Tapestry CSS Support</a>.<br/>
	
	<form t:type="form" t:id="inputs">
		<table>
			<tr>
				<th>First Name:</th>
				<td><input t:type="TextField" t:value="firstName"/></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<th>Last Name:</th>
				<td><input t:type="TextField" t:value="lastName"/></td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</form>
	
	<a t:type="pagelink" t:page="Index" href="#">Home</a><br/><br/>
	
	<t:sourcecodedisplay src="/web/src/main/java/jumpstart/web/pages/examples/styling/Stylesheets.tml"/>
	<t:sourcecodedisplay src="/web/src/main/java/jumpstart/web/pages/examples/styling/Stylesheets.java"/>
</body>
</html>